review_blob: Malty taste dominates this brew.  The finish is very metallic also.  Better than most light beers however.  At 104 cals. per bottle it is a wise calorie spend if you are dieting...it is beer with a 5%abv...not too bad of a taste, and it cuts a few of those nasty carbs and calories out of the mix.  If you are watching your weight this beer is a good choice...if you are not worried about the "gut" then go for something a little hearty, like a Samuel Smiths Oatmeal Stout...yum!

Six months ago I would have rated this beer far worse than I have. I recently had some major weight loss and I intend to keep it off so this beer is perfect...calorie-wise anyway.  It has a touch of skunkiness in the aftertaste and the aroma is "sour" smelling.  But overall it is still beer and it wont put the beer belly back on as quickly.
Once again, a mass produced watered down beer with no real taste.  The aroma was faint, but skunky.  Very pale yellow with quickly deminshing head.   The taste truly reminded me of an ODouls.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: This is my first experience with a Leinenkugel, and Im pleasantly surprised.  There was little aroma with this beer, but it had a few nice amber color with bottles clinging to the side of the glass.  It had a nice hoppy taste with a very good finish.  As I said this was my first Leinenkugel product but it will not be my last.

WTF!!  Why?  Why?  Why must they ruin everything, including beer.  Why would they think that beer is an energy drink.....especially Budweiser.  You can add caffeine and ginseng to a turd and it would still be a turd.  Case in point, this is definetly a turd.  It taste like sugar water, and leaves a nasty after taste.  Did I feel energized?  No, I was too busy trying to get the taste out of my mouth by licking my dogs ass (figure of speech).  Avoid this crap.
Have you ever wondered what happens to the anti-freeze that gets changed from your car at the garage?  Well, I think I found out. The on;y redeeming factor is the cool bottles it comes in.

This is a perfect example of macro brewing at its worst.  This beer has a skunky smell, with no head.  It is see-through, with a nasty taste and finish.  This is also a fine example of a "College Beer", because once you get a job youll never buy this stuff.

Very nice Black & Tan.  Poured with a nice black color with a light cream colored head.  A nutty aroma was really pleasing.  The taste was a little too bitter for my taste, but had a very good finish.  This beer will be come a regular in my Black and Tan buys.

I bought a sixer for $1.99, so I went into this beer not expecting much, however, it wasnt as bad as I had anticipated.  It had a few bubbles that hung to the side of the glass, with a quickly diminishing head.  It had a skunky smell, but the taste wasnt too bad.  Reminded me of a low-end Hefe.  The finish left me without a bitter beer face.  If money runs low in the future, I may revisit this beer.

My loving wife ordered 3 bottles of Westy 12 for my birthday...what a gift it was!!!  This beer had everything.  A dark rich color that couldnt be seen through, a head that lasted the entire time a drank it....in a St Sixtus trappist! (she bought me the glass too!!).  The flavor was outstanding with a rich chocolate/coffee mix.  The aroma was divine.  The finish was great with my whole body warming from the high alcohol content.
The monks who make this at St. Sixtus have truly master their art.  This beer is hard to come by...my wife ordered it from Belgianshop.com, which makes it even more of a treat.  Ive read many say that this beer has been over rated.....WTF....if anything it has been under-rated.  If God was a drinking man, I bet he would drink this.  I have two bottles left, one which i am waiting to age for a year, and the other I plan to drink on the day my first child is born...Jan. 05!!!

Thank you rate beer for changing my palate and educating me on what beer truly is!!

This is the best Molson Ive tried.  For what it is it had a nice malty taste, with a good finish.  Poured nicely with a quick dissolve head.  It had a nice alcohol content without the strong alcohol taste.  Definetly will drink again.
Wow!  This oatmeal stout blew me away.  Very good color, with a very nice smell.  The taste was excellant with its roasty chocolate hints.  Great.

Very nice hefe, but not the best I have ever tried.  This hefe had a very nice color, that sort of cloudy yellow that you find with hefeweizens.  The taste was ok, but left a little to be desired.  Poured very nice, with a very nice head that lasted.

I bought this beer at a gas station, while looking for my usual macro.  It had a very nice looking bottle, and it was strategically placed next to heineken.  We I got home I was suprised to find it had a very nice aroma, and very smooth going down.  It tasted a lot like Heineken, but not as bitter aftertaste.  I was surprised to find a nice lager coming from Anheuser-Busch.  Not my favorite beer, but drinkable.
Not that bad of a dark, and a whole lot better than the regular Heineken lager.
Very nice beer with a fruit complex.  No bitterness noted, with very little aftertaste.
I'm starting a petiton to stop light beer being produced when the original taste like watered down pee.  This beer is taste like a beer burp, and is less filling.
This is another example of watered down, month old beer.  I found it amazing how if you leave a bottle of MGD out without a lid for a month, it taste just like Blatz.
This light isn't the worst on the market.  It is a cheap beer, very watery.  Definetley a lady's beer.
This is simply a cheap beer.  It has been around for years, well at least what I drank was.  This is better than milwaukee's Beast.
UPDATED: AUG 3, 2004
why?  why would you make a light version of a beer that is nasty to begin with....well i know that happens all the time...however this light is easier to stomach than its full flavored counterpart.
if turpintine was made into a beer i'm sure this is what it would taste like.
Another example of great alcohol content but horrible, horrible taste.  this is hobo beer.  best to be drank out of a bag.
this beer is another example of alcohol content verses taste.  this is not to be savored, it is to be chugged and to get messed up on real quick.  a great college beer.
beer_name: Schlitz Red Bull XL Malt Liquor

review_blob: this beer taste awful...with that said i have to say with a 5.9% abv, and a price this cheap...it is ok.
I believe this actually taste better than the original pabst blue ribbon.  not too bad of an ice beer.
Not the worst light beer out there....but pretty shitty in its own right.  Why blue ribbon?  i guess this is why Pabst doesn't own there own brewing company anymore.
This stuff is thick...it has the consistency of coal tar.  Too much of a maple taste for me.  Definetely not a drinking mans drink....reserve this for special occasions only.
Very good seasonal.  This is the type of beer you have around the fire on those cold snowy nights.  Great taste and appearance.
Rolling rock is a light beer, why make a light version of a beer that already taste like water.  These light beers need to be stopped.
Why does Grolsch always smell so bad. The taste is always nice with no aftertaste, but that smell.....gag.
Was not what I was expecting.  Better tasting than most light ice beers...bets the hell out of bud ice light.
This isn't the worst ice beer out ther, but it sure the hell isn't the best.  It is too sweet for an ice beer, but doen't leave much of an after taste.
One of the worst beers ever made.  This stuff works better than ex-lax, and is cheaper.
Quite possibly the worst beer on the planet.  It has the taste of urinal water with the same aroma.  My girlfriend uses this stuff to take her fingernail polish off.
Not a bad spice.  Great taste with an even better finish. Well worth a second tasting.
Not a bad Ice beer.  A little light tasting for my palate, but a good beer all the same.

Why must they make a light beer for every beer made.  This is a perfect example where they should have left well enough alone.  I have always liked Labatt Blue, so I thought I'd try the light..it was heartbreaking to taste this sour water, knowing it was being sold with the Labatt name.
Nice beer, had a hint of a citrus smell and taste.  Defenitely not the best Hefe out there.
Not bad for Michelob.  The aftertaste fades quick.  One of the best Michelob beers out today.
HA HA HA HA HA HA the sadest party of this beer is realizing that I payed for it.  Why does the FDA allow such a product to be mass marketed.
I love the color....black is cool.  The taste is good with just the right amount of bitterness.
UPDATED: DEC 16, 2004

I love the name of this beer....sounds like it is going to be kick ass...however, it is like all Mexican water...dirty yellow, with a not so pleasing aroma.  Also like mexican water, drink enough of this and you will be up all night on the toilet.
Mexican beer has its place...MEXICO, but I have to say this is better than Corona.
Not much different than the other Molson brews out there.  A good Canadian.
This is a light beer, be warned.  However, it is fairly good for being light.  A hell of a lot better than most lights out there.
This is a very lame beer.  Has a very skunky smell initial, but the taste isn't too horribly bad.  Not the best Molson I've had.
Pretty good Hefe, especially from Sam.  However, this beer left a slight aftertaste.
